<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">Dear {!Contact.Name},</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">IATA Code: {!Account.IATACode__c}</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">In reference to advice given to IATA concerning the risks associated with payment card transactions and potential data breaches, there is a need to confirm the compliance of Accredited Agencies operating within the BSP to be Payment Card Industry (PCI) Data Security Standard (DSS) compliant.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">Under the Passenger Sales Agency Rules, all IATA Accredited Agencies must ensure its full compliance with the PCI DSS.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">The PCI DSS, is a global standard aimed at helping merchants (Agency) understand and implement standards for security policies, technologies and ongoing processes that protect their payment systems from breaches and theft of cardholder data.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">In light of the above, you are kindly requested to provide us with your Attestation of Compliance to indicate your company’s compliance.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">We would like to inform you that as per the PCI DSS guidelines, compliance certificates are not recognized for PCI DSS validation. The only documentation recognized for PCI DSS validation are the official documents from the <a href="https://www.pcisecuritystandards.org/">PCI SSC website</a>. <b><u>Any other form of certificate or documentation issued for the purposes of illustrating compliance to PCI DSS or any other PCI standard are not authorized or validated.</u></b></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">The Attestation of Compliance is the document used to indicate that the appropriate Report on Compliance or Self-assessment Questionnaire has been performed, and to attest to your organization’s compliance status with PCI DSS.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><br></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">For further information about how to become PCI DSS compliance please visit our PCI DSS dedicated web page: http://www.iata.org/services/finance/Pages/pci-dss.aspx</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">In case you are currently not processing any transactions through BSP utilizing Credit Card form of payment and not intending to do so, you can submit the Nil Credit Card Self-Declaration, attached to this communication.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">Please note that IATA will monitor your Agency’s sales reports to ensure that no credit card transactions are processed through BSP.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">The above requested documentation (Attestation of Compliance or Nil Credit Card Self-Declaration) should be sent to IATA through our Customer Service Portal web page: http://www.iata.org/cs to arrive no later than {!Today() + 30}. Please attach a scanned copy to case {!AMS_OSCAR__c.Name} visible on your portal home page under ‘My recent cases’ section.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">The Agency Management Department will carry out a review, and make a decision based upon the evidence available.</font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><b>Please note that failure to comply with this requirement per IATA’s request will result in an Administrative Non-Compliance being issued against the Agency.</b></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></p><p class="MsoNormal"><font face="arial" size="2">We would appreciate you will give this matter your immediate attention. Should you need any further information from IATA, please do not hesitate to login a new query via our Customer Portal: www.iata.org/cs.&nbsp;</font></p>]]></td>
</tr>
</table>